# Discord entity formatting

In user-facing embeds and messages, always render Discord resources with native mention syntax — never plain names, tags, or raw IDs alone.

Use helpers from `bot/src/utils/guild-display.ts`:

| Entity | Helper | Output |
|---|---|---|
| Role (by ID) | `formatRole(guild, roleId)` | `<@&roleId>` |
| Role (object) | `formatRoleFromRole(role)` | `<@&roleId>` |
| Text/announcement channel | `formatChannel(guild, channelId)` | `<#channelId>` |
| Category | `formatCategory(guild, categoryId)` | `<#categoryId>` |
| User (by ID) | `formatUser(userId)` | `<@userId>` |
| User (object) | `formatUserFromUser(user)` | `<@userId>` |
| Guild member | `formatMember(member)` | `<@userId>` |

## Rules

- Do **not** use `role.name`, `user.tag`, `user.username`, or `channel.name` in embed descriptions or reply text shown to users.
- Prefer helpers over inline `` `<@&${id}>` `` so deleted/missing resources show consistent fallbacks.
- CSV/Excel exports and audit log filenames may keep plain text identifiers — that is not user-facing Discord UI.
- Slash command mentions use `</name:id>` via `formatHelpEntry` in `bot-info.ts`.

## Text emphasis and readability

User-facing embeds and messages may use Discord markdown to improve clarity:

| Style | Syntax | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| Bold | `**text**` | Team names, tournament names, labels, counts |
| Italic | `*text*` | Secondary notes, stage labels, helper copy |
| Underline | `__text__` | Separators such as `__vs__`, section dividers |
| Monospace | `` `text` `` | Scores, Match IDs, channel slugs, raw numbers |

Use helpers from `bot/src/utils/match-formatting.ts` for bracket/score UI:

- `formatEmphasizedName(name)` — bold team or player name (escapes markdown)
- `formatScoreValue(score)` — monospace score so it never blends with names like `team 2`
- `formatMatchupTitle(team1, team2)` — `**team 1** __vs__ **team 2**`
- `formatMatchScoreBlock(...)` — multi-line score with winner marker

### Score formatting rules

- **Never** write `team 2 3 - 5 team 1` in plain text — names ending in digits become ambiguous.
- **Always** separate names and scores: `**team 2** · \`3\`` or use `formatMatchScoreBlock`.
- Put scores in backticks; put team/tournament names in bold.
- Optional notes use italics: `*Nota del staff*`.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
`Role: **${role.name}**`
`${member.displayName} (@${member.user.username})`
`Owner: ${owner.user.tag}`

// ✅ GOOD
`Role: ${formatRoleFromRole(role)}`
formatUser(member.id)
formatUserFromUser(owner.user)

// ❌ BAD — ambiguous when team names contain numbers
`Score: team 2 3 - 5 team 1`

// ✅ GOOD
formatMatchScoreBlock({ team1Name: 'team 2', team2Name: 'team 1', score1: 3, score2: 5, winnerSide: 2 })
```
